09/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The Agency for Nuclear Regulation (ANR) has made an upward revision to its assessment of a 1 March problem with the 5th reactor at the Kozloduy nuclear power station. 
According to ANR chief Sergey Tsochev, the event was re-assessed Monday (8 May) and categorised as a level 2 ("Incident"). 
Previously, it had been placed at level 1 ("Anomaly"). 
He said that at present the unit is working safely. 
(Dnevnik, Mediapool - 08/05/06)
